# QuantaPy Package Notes

QuantaPy is organized around small orchestrators and registered plugin
components:

```text
orchestrator -> coordinates workflow
core         -> shared containers and base classes
modules      -> registered providers, transforms, signals, orders, simulations
registry     -> component registration
```

The current workflow is explicit compute-then-commit:

```python
data = Data()
data.add_provider("Market", "OHLC", "FMP", source_ids=["AAPL"], interval="1hour")

store = DataStore()
for name, dataset in data.fetch().items():
    store.add_raw(name, dataset, source={"provider": "OHLC"})

calc = Calculator()
calc.add_transform("Technical", "Moving Average", name="SMA_20", timeperiod=20)

indicators = calc.derive_combined(store, "OHLC_AAPL")
store.add_child(
    "OHLC_AAPL-AllIndicators",
    indicators,
    parent_ids=["OHLC_AAPL"],
    kind="derived",
)
```

Only `DataStore.add_raw()` and `DataStore.add_child()` commit data to the store.
Providers, transformers, calculators, strategies, and simulations return outputs
first so scripts and GUIs can preview results before committing them.

